<subSubSection id="50A46512FFE3FFE19296D7062BCD52EA" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="2" pageNumber="270" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="18013699FFE3FFE19296D7062F78564F" blockId="2.[136,1452,1852,2059]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,158,1445]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="2" pageNumber="270">
Diagnosis:—The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DFBE4D1AFFE3FFE09094D7072D375018" box="[650,866,1852,1878]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="2" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cathcartii">
<emphasis id="2ACAEA8BFFE3FFE09094D7072D375018" box="[650,866,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="270">Begonia cathcartii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having pseudo-opposite leaves subtending the inflorescence, and having tepals which are pilose abaxially. It differs in having denser hairs on the upper leaf surface which are much shorter, giving the leaf a rough appearance (not glossy); tepals which although pilose abaxially have shorter and more sparse hairs, and sparser and shorter hairs on the petioles and peduncles; it is also a smaller plant i.e. less than 
<quantity id="DF469B7CFFE3FFE092ECD7F62F6D50A9" box="[242,312,1996,2023]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="270" unit="cm" value="30.0">30 cm</quantity>
(vs. up to 
<quantity id="DF469B7CFFE3FFE093AAD7F62FAF50A9" box="[436,506,1996,2023]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="270" unit="cm" value="60.0">60 cm</quantity>
tall) and has shorter internodes i.e. less than 
<quantity id="DF469B7CFFE3FFE091E2D7F62A6150A9" box="[1020,1076,1996,2023]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="270" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
long on the erect stem (vs. up to 
<quantity id="DF469B7CFFE3FFE09296D7CA2E875F45" box="[136,210,2032,2059]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="270" unit="cm" value="23.0">23 cm</quantity>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="DFBE4D1AFFE3FFE09394D7CB2C1C5F44" authorityName="Qian" authorityYear="2001" box="[394,585,2032,2058]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="2" pageNumber="270" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="menglianensis">
<emphasis id="2ACAEA8BFFE3FFE09394D7CB2C1C5F44" box="[394,585,2032,2058]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="270">B. menglianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having cauline leaves on the inflorescence (vs. absent), white ovaries with sparse red pilose hairs (vs. red or green ovaries which are glabrous), sparser and shorter white (vs. denser and longer red) pilose indumentum on the petioles and veins on the lower leaf surface, and leaves with an acuminate (vs. rounded to acute) apex.
</paragraph>
